  "_about": "Four FailureModes for the sulis-plugins-marketplace release-train Workflow, after the trunk re-model (CH-01KT4K). Three encode today's lived defects (CH-01KSYZ workflow-yaml-fails-to-parse, CH-01KSZ1 loop-guard-matches-founder-pr, GH-token tag bot-tag-doesnt-trigger-release-prod); one (version-drift-detected-pre-flight) guards the in-branch version-file agreement check. The four dev->main-PR FailureModes (pr-checks-fail, release-pr-conflicts-with-target-at-merge, pr-open-but-mergeability-stuck, probabilistic-step-token-budget-exceeded) were deleted — they were orphaned when the five dev->main-PR Steps were removed (there is no release PR to fail checks / conflict / stick, and no probabilistic Step on the trunk). The loop-guard + bot-tag FailureModes are KEPT and load-bearing on a trunk: deleting them re-introduces the release-of-release loop (#132) and the downstream-trigger bug. Schema: plugins/sulis/brain/compiled/foundation/failuremode.schema.json. Tenant ULID is deterministic — derived as SHA256('tenant-name:sulis-plugins-marketplace') mapped to Crockford base32 (first char clamped to 0 per ULID spec); reused by every release-train canonical instance.",
  "captured_on": "2026-06-01",

  "failuremodes": [
    {
      "id": "dna:failuremode:01KTR5NAFM3BGKRJTV1RTJD2MY",
      "sys_status": "active",
      "name": "workflow-yaml-fails-to-parse",
      "for_domain": "dna:tenant:6XBZ93FSHN5TRX8MCS5R66FNCM",
      "kind": "invalid-input",
      "description": "release-on-merge.yml fails to parse — typically because an inline shell snippet contains an unescaped colon or a heredoc that conflicts with YAML's flow syntax. CH-01KSYZ regression: PR #130 silently skipped because the YAML at HEAD didn't parse; GitHub Actions silently no-ops on parse failure. Recovery: abort the dispatch + surface the YAML parse error to the founder so the malformed file can be reverted or fixed.",
      "recovery_strategy": "abort",
      "recovery_detail": "Drift detector + branch-ci.yml MUST run pyyaml safe-load against release-on-merge.yml on every PR and fail the build on parse failure. This is the second line of defense; the first is the founder-typed lint at edit time. On parse failure: PR cannot land until release-on-merge.yml parses.",
      "expected_frequency": "rare",
      "blocks_progress": true,
      "state": "active",
      "valid_from": "2026-06-01T00:00:00Z",
      "confidence": 0.95
    },
    {
      "id": "dna:failuremode:01KTRA7VTSP3E14MZ4S641NHQ5",
      "sys_status": "active",
      "name": "loop-guard-matches-founder-pr",
      "for_domain": "dna:tenant:6XBZ93FSHN5TRX8MCS5R66FNCM",
      "kind": "policy-violation",
      "description": "release-on-merge's loop-guard regex (designed to skip its own previously-created release PRs to prevent infinite release-of-release-of-release loops) over-matches and skips a founder-authored PR whose title or body happens to contain the loop-guard's trigger pattern. CH-01KSZ1 regression: PR #132 was a founder PR that title-matched the bot's release-PR prefix and got skipped. Recovery: tighten the loop-guard regex (require bot-author or release-branch-prefix match in addition to title-prefix); abort the current dispatch when guard would skip a non-bot-authored PR.",
      "recovery_strategy": "abort",
      "recovery_detail": "Loop-guard regex MUST require BOTH (a) title-prefix match AND (b) actor=='github-actions[bot]' OR head_ref starts with 'release/'. Single-condition matches no longer skip. Drift detector verifies release-on-merge.yml encodes the both-conditions check.",
      "expected_frequency": "rare",
      "blocks_progress": true,
      "state": "active",
      "valid_from": "2026-06-01T00:00:00Z",
      "confidence": 0.95
    },
    {
      "id": "dna:failuremode:01KTRGB53ME08DPVBZ03RTS359",
      "sys_status": "active",
      "name": "bot-tag-doesnt-trigger-release-prod",
      "for_domain": "dna:tenant:6XBZ93FSHN5TRX8MCS5R66FNCM",
      "kind": "authorisation-denied",
      "description": "release-on-merge creates a git tag (v*.*.*) using GITHUB_TOKEN, but GitHub Actions' default GITHUB_TOKEN is denied permission to trigger downstream workflows (release-prod.yml) when pushing tags. This is a documented GitHub Actions security boundary, not a bug: bot-created refs do not fire workflow events by design. Recovery: fall back to a manual `gh release create` step that the founder runs to create the actual release artifact, OR swap GITHUB_TOKEN for a PAT (deferred — secret-management implication).",
      "recovery_strategy": "fallback",
      "recovery_detail": "release-on-merge.yml emits the tag + a journal entry instructing the founder to run `gh release create v<ver> --generate-notes`. The /sulis:release-train skill surfaces the deferred step in its summary. Future automation: PAT-scoped secret + bot identity rotation (deferred to a separate WP; out of scope for the canonical encoding).",
      "expected_frequency": "frequent",
      "blocks_progress": false,
      "state": "active",
      "valid_from": "2026-06-01T00:00:00Z",
      "confidence": 0.9
    },
    {
      "id": "dna:failuremode:01KTRNPG3DAPH7BW0CAQ05C3PH",
      "sys_status": "active",
      "name": "version-drift-detected-pre-flight",
      "for_domain": "dna:tenant:6XBZ93FSHN5TRX8MCS5R66FNCM",
      "kind": "policy-violation",
      "description": "Pre-flight check finds plugin.json.version disagrees with the matching entry in .claude-plugin/marketplace.json's plugins[].version, OR with the corresponding changeset's claimed version-bump. Typical cause: prior half-bump (a previous release-train run bumped plugin.json but failed before marketplace.json got updated, leaving the two artifacts out of sync). Recovery: abort the release; surface the specific version disagreement to the founder; founder reconciles (either manually re-running the failed sync step or accepting the version that's already shipped and bumping the other).",
      "recovery_strategy": "abort",
      "recovery_detail": "Pre-flight Step compares (plugin.json.version, marketplace.json[plugin].version, latest-changeset.version-bump-target). Three-way disagreement → abort with a table of the three values. Two-way disagreement (most common: plugin.json ahead, marketplace.json behind) → abort and tell founder to run the sync step manually.",
      "expected_frequency": "rare",
      "blocks_progress": true,
      "state": "active",
      "valid_from": "2026-06-01T00:00:00Z",
      "confidence": 0.9
    }
  ]
